India’s Ahluwalia Says It’s ‘Best’ to Auction Telecom Licenses

-- B y   T u s h a r   D h a r a
-- 
2011-10-21T05:44:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/india-s-ahluwalia-says-it-s-best-to-auction-telecom-licenses.html
Montek Singh Ahluwalia , deputy
chairman of  India ’s Planning Commission, said the “best”
option for the government is to auction the telecommunications
licenses which are coming up for renewal in 2014.  The Telecom Regulatory Authority of India and the Telecom
Commission will help the government form the license renewal
policy, Ahluwalia said in an interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tushar Dhara in  New Delhi  at 
 tdhara1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
